http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/Call-for-fight-against-anti-ryot-policies/article14009403.ece

All India Kisan Sabha (AIKS) vice-president Sarampalli Malla Reddy has called for a joint and consistent struggle by the Telangana Rythu Sangham, Vyavasaya Karmika Sangham and CITU against the “anti-farmer” and “anti-worker” policies of both State and Central governments. A mass movement involving farmers, agricultural labourers, workers and other toiling masses should be organised to exert pressure on the State and Central governments shun the “anti-working class” policies, he said.He was speaking at a district-level convention organised by the Rythu Sangham, Vyavasaya Karmika Sangham and CITU here on Tuesday.